This paper deals with the problem of maximum rate achievable with analog network coding in a wireless relay network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The paper also discusses the performance of analog network coding in specific network scenarios, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves computations and optimization techniques, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
